title: Google\Cloud\Bigtable\Admin\V2\HotTablet
name: HotTablet
description:
A tablet is a defined by a start and end key and is explained in https://cloud.google.com/bigtable/docs/overview#architecture and https://cloud.google.com/bigtable/docs/performance#optimization.

A Hot tablet is a tablet that exhibits high average cpu usage during the time interval from start time to end time.

Generated from protobuf message google.bigtable.admin.v2.HotTablet

Extends Google\Protobuf\Internal\Message

params.name: data
params.description: Optional. Data for populating the Message object.

params.name: data.name
params.description: The unique name of the hot tablet. Values are of the form projects/{project}/instances/{instance}/clusters/{cluster}/hotTablets/[a-zA-Z0-9_-]*.

params.name: data.table_name
params.description: Name of the table that contains the tablet. Values are of the form projects/{project}/instances/{instance}/tables/[_a-zA-Z0-9][-_.a-zA-Z0-9]*.

params.name: data.start_time
params.description: Output only. The start time of the hot tablet.

params.name: data.end_time
params.description: Output only. The end time of the hot tablet.

params.name: data.node_cpu_usage_percent
params.description: Output only. The average CPU usage spent by a node on this tablet over the start_time to end_time time range. The percentage is the amount of CPU used by the node to serve the tablet, from 0% (tablet was not interacted with) to 100% (the node spent all cycles serving the hot tablet).
